    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nSay I have a package, `mainpkg`, that depends on a pxd file, `test.pxd` in another package, `deppkg`, like this\n\n```cython\nfrom deppkg.test cimport Test\n```\n\nwhere `deppkg/test.pxd` is:\n\n```cython\ncdef class Test:\n\tint x\n```\n\nIf I install `deppkg` as editable, using `pip install -e deppkg`, and then try to run\n\n```\npip install mainpkg --no-build-isolation\n```\n\n(`--no-build-isolation` is necessary because I need the pxd file at build time), Cython fails to find `deppkg/test.pxd` with this error\n\n```\nError compiling Cython file:\n------------------------------------------------------------\n...\nfrom deppkg.test cimport Test\n^\n------------------------------------------------------------\nmainpkg/test.pyx:1:0: 'deppkg/test.pxd' not found\nCompiling ./mainpkg/test.pyx because it changed.\n[1/1] Cythonizing ./mainpkg/test.pyx\n```\n\nIf I install `deppkg` without the `-e` flag, I can build `mainpkg`.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\nIt's all in the repo at https://github.com/cpcloud/cython-editable-bug\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nI would expect the build-time behavior of a dependency to be not dependent on whether a package is installed editably or not.\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.2.1\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
